##############################################################################
# 03_WGCNA_module_biology_hubs_enrichment_FINAL_v4.R
#
# TITLE
# Biological interpretation of GENE-COLLAPSED WGCNA modules
# (hubs + functional enrichment + optional network export)
#
# PURPOSE
# This script takes the final WGCNA objects generated by Script 02 and performs:
#   1) kME / module membership calculation
#   2) hub prioritization within WGCNA modules
#   3) robust functional enrichment by module: GO BP, KEGG, Reactome
#   4) export of node tables for optional STRING/Cytoscape analysis
#
# IMPORTANT
# This script uses modules generated from GENE-COLLAPSED features.
# It does NOT use aptamer-level WGCNA modules.
#
# KEY UPDATE IN v3/v4
# Enrichment is no longer allowed to fail silently or return only zeros without
# diagnostic files. The script now:
#   - maps SYMBOL -> ENTREZID robustly
#   - runs enrichment with permissive cutoffs to retrieve candidate terms
#   - exports all terms, significant terms, and top terms separately
#   - counts FDR-significant terms for module prioritization
#   - writes error messages per module/library if enrichment fails
#   - uses real module colors in hub figures and node tables
#   - v4 fixes vectorized module color assignment
#
# INPUTS FROM SCRIPT 02
#   WGCNA_Workflow_april_V2/results/02_WGCNA_core_collapsed_genes/
#     - workspace/wgcna_core_collapsed_workspace.RData
#     - tables/gene_module_assignment.csv
#
# MAIN OUTPUTS
#   WGCNA_Workflow_april_V2/results/03_WGCNA_module_biology_hubs_enrichment/
#     - tables/full_kME_table_wide.csv
#     - tables/full_kME_assigned_module_long.csv
#     - tables/module_hub_summary.csv
#     - tables/enrichment_summary_by_module.csv
#     - hubs/top_hubs_<module>.csv
#     - enrichment/GO_BP/*.csv
#     - enrichment/KEGG/*.csv
#     - enrichment/Reactome/*.csv
#     - figures/hubs/*.pdf/png
#     - figures/enrichment/*.pdf/png
#     - network_optional/nodes_top_hubs_<module>.csv
#
# AUTHOR
# Matías Pizarro + ChatGPT support
##############################################################################

